<item>
            <title>[LU-2566] test: sanity-gss: need to execute test-framework.sh before invoke error() at line 21</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2566</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am testing sanity-gss.sh on sles11sp2. It failed correctly and tried to print an error message at line 21:&lt;br/&gt;
   error &quot;unsupported kernel (gss only works with 2.6.x)&quot; ;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that error() is defined in test-framework.sh, which has not been executed yet. So, instead of proper error message I got:&lt;br/&gt;
    error: Command not found&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="17075">LU-2566</key>
            <summary>test: sanity-gss: need to execute test-framework.sh before invoke error() at line 21</summary>
