                            <comment id="50706" author="adilger" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2013 13:53:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch has landed for 2.4.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49917" author="bogl" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 20:44:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4947&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4947&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49915" author="bogl" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 20:35:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This one looks easy enough.  Just need to move the kernel version test down a few lines in the test script to after all the simple init takes place.  Then the error() function will be defined and available before it&apos;s used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will work up a simple patch to do this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49913" author="pjones" created="Thu, 3 Jan 2013 20:18:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
